HEADWORD: Corinth
<hw>Cor"inth</hw> <pr>(k?r"?nth)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Corinthus</ets>, Gr. <?/<?/<?/<?/. Cf. <er>Currant</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A city of Greece, famed for its luxury and
extravagance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A small fruit; a currant.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Broome.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corinthiac</ent>⟦br⟧
